conversation_history.content: i am sad my friend called me ugly

I'm sorry to hear that you're feeling this way. It sounds like you might be personalizing what your friend said. Remember, someone's comment about you doesn't define your worth or beauty. A practical step could be to write down three things that you like about yourself every day to help build your self-esteem.
it's even worse because i am in horrible traffic and need to get home to my sister's bday party

I understand that being stuck in traffic while having somewhere important to be can be really frustrating. Your thoughts seem to be catastrophizing, or imagining the worst-case scenario. Try to remember that everyone experiences unexpected delays and it doesn't make you a bad person or sister. To help manage your stress, you could try deep breathing exercises while you wait in traffic.
